# Code conventions

## Comments

- Write **all code comments** (inline, block, JSDoc) in **English**.
- User-facing copy (UI labels, library descriptions, docs/wiki) may stay in Polish when the product language is Polish.
- Keep comments brief; explain non-obvious intent, not what the code already states.

```css
/* ❌ Layout — poza domyślną skalą spacing Tailwinda */
/* ✅ Layout — outside Tailwind's default spacing scale */
```

## Tailwind `@theme` tokens

Prefer Tailwind defaults when values match 1:1. Only add custom tokens when the design system needs something Tailwind does not provide. Full DS rules: `tailwind-design-system.mdc`.

**Use Tailwind defaults for:**
- Font sizes: `text-xs` (12px), `text-sm` (14px), `text-base` (16px), `text-lg` (18px)
- Spacing scale: `p-2`, `gap-4`, `bottom-4`, etc.
- Semantic colors in components: `neutral-*`, `gold-*` directly — avoid redundant `--color-bg` / `--color-text` aliases

**Keep custom `@theme` tokens for:**
- Brand color scales (`neutral-*`, `gold-*`)
- Fluid typography (`display-xl`, `h1`–`h3` clamps)
- Brand-only sizes (`text-ui` 15px, `text-h4` 22px)
- Layout tokens outside the spacing scale (`spacing-gutter`, `spacing-section`, `spacing-header-h`)
- Brand shadows (`shadow-subtle`, `shadow-1`, `shadow-2`)
- Brand motion (`ease-luxury`, `duration-fast/base/slow`)
- Focus ring offsets used across components

When removing a custom token, update `@utility` helpers, `tailwind-merge` extensions in `cn.ts`, and all component class names in the same change.
